---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Title from '../components/Title.astro';
import json from '../database.json';
import ModPreview from '../components/ModPreview.astro';
---

<Layout title="DREDGE Mod Manager">
	<main>
        <Title title="Mod Manager" />
        
        <div class="w-100 justify-content-center d-flex">
			<div class="w-md-50">
				<div class="d-flex align-items-center">
					<img src="/images/mod manager.png" class="w-100 ratio ratio-1x1"></img>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
				
		<br/>

		<div class="justify-content-center d-flex">
			<a href="https://github.com/xen-42/DredgeModManager/releases" class="btn btn-info rounded ps-4 pe-4 p-2"><h2>Click here to download the Mod Manager</h2></a>
		</div>

		<br/>

		<div class="w-100 justify-content-center d-flex">
			<div class="w-md-50">

				The mod manager allows you to:
				<ul>
					<li>Download and install mods, including the mod loader itself</li>
					<li>Update mods</li>
					<li>Enable or disable mods</li>
					<li>Launch the game directly with your enabled mods</li>
				</ul>

				To use the manager:
				<ul>
					<li>Download the correct version from the link above. If you're on windows this will likely be "Dredge.Mod.Manager_#.#.#_x64-setup.exe".</li>
					<li>Run the installer. If on Windows, Microsoft Defender will stop you from running it. Click "more info" and "run anyway".</li>
					<li>Click through the installer as normal.</li>
				</ul>

				<b>Note:</b> You must install Winch from the Available mods list to have any mods take work. To get rid of all mods, uninstall all of them including Winch
				 and then verify your game files in 
				whatever platform you installed the game with.
			</div>
		</div>

		<br/>

	</main>
</Layout>


